message.1
	Good morning Mr. Phelps. Your Mission (should you decide to\naccept it) is to prevent this automated nuclear reactor\nfrom being destroyed by a saboteur's TIME BOMB!\n
message.2
	Nothing happened
message.3
	My bomb detector
message.4
	wails ALARMINGLY!
message.5
	CLICK!
message.6
	I can't do that
message.7
	It appears locked
message.8
	button is now unlocked
message.9
	Blue
message.10
	Yellow
message.11
	There's a Bright flash & I hear something fall to the floor.\nI can't see what it is from here though.\n
message.12
	*   B O O O O O O O O O M ! * * * * * *
message.13
	The saboteur (who also rewired the security system) is a heart\npatient. He plans to SUICIDE with the reactor! He is still loosein the building.\nYou'll find Security keys & a map in the manila envelope lying\nnext to the tape player.
message.14
	politely beeps...\n
message.15
	angrily buzzes...\n
message.16
	Strange...
message.17
	Most doors & windows are under automated security control.
message.18
	Metallic voice says:
message.19
	`Show authorization please`\n
message.20
	`Authorization INSUFFICIENT for access`\n
message.21
	The door opens just long enough for me to scurry through.
message.22
	I'm on the 2nd floor. Below I see the control room surronding\nthe reactor core. There's a wide ledge just under the window.
message.23
	In this Adventure there's NO score. Either you make it or ...\n
message.24
	Tell me with what? Example: `WITH FIST`
message.25
	Be sure I'm carrying it!
message.26
	Recorder goes flying thru the glass landing in the control room.Boy what a MESS!\n
message.27
	Click!\nRoom lights dim and a screen drops from the ceiling.\nYou hear a hidden projector start.
message.28
	The screen illuminates for awhile, but no movie!?
message.29
	The projector stops, the screen rises, and the lights return.
message.30
	A movie runs telling about the reactor and its construction\ninteresting highlights:\n1) Plastic DEFORMS strangely in radiation\n2) Even short exposure to HIGH radiation is LETHAL, so suit up\n
message.31
	The radiation did something to my pail!
message.32
	Holding a Radiation Suit
message.33
	doesn't provide much protection for me\nas I fall down retching I hear/FEEL THE BOMB explode!\n
message.34
	Welcome to Adventure number 3 `MISSION IMPOSSIBLE`\nby Scott Adams, Dedicated to Maegen Adams.\n
message.35
	A business suit
message.36
	I'm WEARING an anti-radiation suit.
message.37
	It won't budge!
message.38
	Something won't fit thru the door.
message.39
	I turn the knob and push
message.40
	gently on the door
message.41
	hard on the door
message.42
	it opens slightly
message.43
	its closed
message.44
	the water spills on the bomb and
message.45
	the control panel which immediately shorts out triggering\nthe bomb
message.46
	defuses it! FANTASTIC, You completed an IMPOSSIBLE mission!
message.47
	the water soaks into the floor
message.48
	say again & use a color!
message.49
	I'm looking into the control room. I notice that the door is\nblocked by some debris.
message.50
	In the distance you hear a dull thud; as if someone fell or\ndropped something heavy.
message.51
	Something fell to the floor.
message.52
	its unreadable
message.53
	its still connected
message.54
	Oh Boy...I think I did something...
message.55
	It made an odd sound.
message.56
	`TV deactivated`\n
message.57
	I don't know where to look
message.58
	Tell me how?
message.59
	Try starting it.
message.60
	Maybe I should FRISK him?
message.61
	Its a seamless box with 1 small hole for the red wire.
message.62
	TV camera is slow scanning the window area.
message.63
	TV camera is powered down.\n
message.64
	It seems safe. Shall I sit down?
message.65
	Only help I can think of is to: `Examine everything closely!`\n
message.66
	I see nothing special.
message.67
	HUH?
message.68
	A minute ago someone ran out of this room! By the way I seem\nto be carrying something!\n
message.69
	Someone came in the room, he saw me and ran out!
message.70
	I see no one here.
message.71
	`Owner of badge is not present!`
message.72
	Hi! Look for Adventure number 4: `VOODOO CASTLE` at your\nfavorite computer store! (Now back to our current program.)
message.73
	Final countdown starts in
message.74
	turns!
message.75
	Some time passes...
message.76
	There is something written there
message.77
	OW! That HURT! Anyway
message.78
	`ACCEPTED`
